<p>The three <a href="/wiki/Rhotic" title="Rhotic">rhotics</a> have been described as voiced and voiceless trills plus a lax English-type approximant. However, Ladefoged<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> found all three to be approximants, with the voiced-voiceless pair being <a href="/wiki/Raised_(phonetics)" title="Raised (phonetics)" class="mw-redirect">raised</a> (without being fricatives) and perhaps at a slightly different <a href="/wiki/Place_of_articulation" title="Place of articulation">place of articulation</a> compared to the third, but not trills.</p>
<p>The Edo alphabet has separate letters for the nasalized allophones of <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/ʋ/</span> and <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/l/</span>, <i>mw</i> and <i>n</i>:</p>
